item.title: SEA-NG
item.description: Drawing deep inspiration from Microsoft's Project Natick , I’ve embarked on an ambitious journey to create the aquatic counterpart of a HomeLab. Here’s the vision: a pressure cooker transformed into a compact, sub-aquatic server, linked to my boat by a dual-purpose fiber optic/power cable whenever I’m moored or anchored. And, of course, I’ll ensure it’s safely aboard while navigating! This endeavor isn’t just about overcoming a unique challenge - it’s the launching pad for a series of future undertakings.
